
  -----------------
  Development Setup
  -----------------


  The repository only contains source material. Some files need to be generated
  when running under Eclipse

  To use within a shell window
  -----------------------------
  No changes needed. Simply invoke buildr compile, buildr test, etc


  Eclipse Settup
  ------------------------
  1) Generate the project and classpath files using
       buildr eclipse

  2) Then generate the ant script (thin shell calling BuildR) using:
       buildr ant

  3) Start Eclipse, import the project (do not copy to workspace).

  4) Specify your Maven repository to Eclipse
     Go to File -> Preferences, Java/Build Path/Class Path Variables and
     add the following variable
       M2_REPO = <path to the local Maven repository>

     On a Mac, the path is typically /Users/<username>/.m2/repository

  5) Tasks can then be called from within Eclipse
       using the Ant panel.

